      • copyTo

        public abstract ImageCore copyTo(ImageCore destinationImage)
        Description copied from interface: ImageDomainTransform
        Copies this image into another image, which must have been previously allocated. The size of the destination image must agree in all dimensions with the size the original image, and the two images must have same bitdepth. The destination image's calibration and other metadata is merged with that of the original image (and replace for parameters that already exist in the destination image's metadata). The implementation might require that both source and destination images should be defined on the same Image Processing Framework (i.e. Created by the same ImageCore factory).
        Specified by:
        copyTo in interface ImageDomainTransform
        Parameters:
        destinationImage - The destination image into which the voxels gray levels should be copies, swapping two coordinates in the voxels' domain.
        Returns:
        The reference to destinationImage for use in the cascade pattern
        See Also:
        ImageDomainTransform.copyTo(wrapScienceJ.wrapImaJ.core.ImageCore)

      • getAxisSwapped

        public ImageCore getAxisSwapped(CoordinateAxis axis1,
                                CoordinateAxis axis2)
        Description copied from interface: ImageDomainTransform
        Constructs a copy of this image with two axis swapped. This amounts to performing a symmetry over the domain of the image. For example, if I1 is the input image with size (w, h, d), and if the input axis are Y and Z, we get an image I2 with size, (w, d, h), and such that I2(x, y, z) = I1(x, z, y). Most of the time and in general, this operation requires re-allocating, and this method systematically allocates a new image without modifying the input image.
        Specified by:
        getAxisSwapped in interface ImageDomainTransform
        Parameters:
        axis1 - The first axis to be swapped
        axis2 - The second axis to be swapped
        Returns:
        The image with swapped axis
        See Also:
        ImageDomainTransform.getAxisSwapped(wrapScienceJ.wrapImaJ.core.CoordinateAxis, wrapScienceJ.wrapImaJ.core.CoordinateAxis)

      • copyAxisSwapped

        public ImageCore copyAxisSwapped(ImageCore destinationImage,
                                 CoordinateAxis axis1,
                                 CoordinateAxis axis2)
        Description copied from interface: ImageDomainTransform
        Copies this image into another image, with two axis swapped. This amounts to performing a symmetry over the domain of the image. For example, if I1 is the input image with size (w, h, d), and if the input axis are Y and Z, we get an image I2 with size, (w, d, h), and such that I2(x, y, z) = I1(x, z, y). This method is intended to avoid a new image allocation in using ImageDomainTransform.getAxisSwapped(CoordinateAxis, CoordinateAxis) when an image with the right dimensions has already been allocated and can be reused. The size of the destination image must agree with the swapped size of the original image, and the two images must have same bitdepth. Furthermore, the destination image's calibration and other metadata is left unchanged.
        Specified by:
        copyAxisSwapped in interface ImageDomainTransform
        Parameters:
        destinationImage - The destination image into which the voxels gray levels should be copied, swapping two coordinates in the voxels' domain. Note that in case axis1 is equal to axis2, the method performs a mere copy, which might be less efficient than ImageDomainTransform.copyTo(ImageCore).
        axis1 - The first axis to be swapped
        axis2 - The second axis to be swapped
        Returns:
        The reference to destinationImage for use in the cascade pattern
        See Also:
        ImageDomainTransform.copyAxisSwapped(wrapScienceJ.wrapImaJ.core.ImageCore, wrapScienceJ.wrapImaJ.core.CoordinateAxis, wrapScienceJ.wrapImaJ.core.CoordinateAxis)

      • copyInto

        public ImageCore copyInto(ImageCore destinationImage,
                          VoxelInt shiftMargin,
                          boolean scaleForBitDepth)
        Description copied from interface: ImageDomainTransform
        Copies this image into another image, which must have been previously allocated. The voxel's coordinates of the input image are translated (shifted) before being copied into the destination image. The two images must have same bit depth, but no requirement is made on the respective sizes of the two images. If the destination voxel does not exist, it is dropped. The destination image's calibration and other metadata is merged with that of the original image (and replace for parameters that already exist in the destination image's metadata). The implementation might require that both source and destination images should be defined on the same Image Processing Framework (i.e. Created by the same ImageCore factory).
        Specified by:
        copyInto in interface ImageDomainTransform
        Parameters:
        destinationImage - The destination image into which the voxels gray levels should be copies, swapping two coordinates in the voxels' domain.
        shiftMargin - The destination voxel Vd has coordinates (Vs + shiftMargin), where Vs is the source voxel's coordinate vector.
        scaleForBitDepth - If true and the two images involved have different bit depth, the colors is multiplied or divided by 256 to adjust gray scales.
        Returns:
        The reference to destinationImage for use in the cascade pattern
        See Also:
        ImageDomainTransform.copyInto(wrapScienceJ.wrapImaJ.core.ImageCore, wrapScienceJ.wrapImaJ.core.VoxelInt, boolean)

      • getPlaneRotated90

        public ImageCore getPlaneRotated90(CoordinateAxis axis1,
                                   CoordinateAxis axis2)
        Description copied from interface: ImageDomainTransform
        Constructs a copy of this image, with the planes generated by two axis rotated. This amounts to swapping the two axis and reversing the second, thus sending the first axis direction vector onto the second one, and sending the second axis direction onto the opposite of the first one. For example, if I1 is the input image with size (w, h, d), and if the input axis are Y and Z, we get an image I2 with size, (w, d, h), and such that I2(x, y, z) = I1(x, d-1-z, y). Most of the time and in general, this operation requires re-allocating, and this method systematically allocates a new image without modifying the input image. Use ImageDomainTransform.copyPlaneRotated90(ImageCore, CoordinateAxis, CoordinateAxis) if no allocation is really required. Note that in case axis1 is equal to axis2, the method performs a mere symmetry, which might be less efficient than ImageDomainTransform.getAxisReversed(CoordinateAxis[]) with a single axis.
        Specified by:
        getPlaneRotated90 in interface ImageDomainTransform
        Parameters:
        axis1 - The first axis to be rotated and sent onto the second
        axis2 - The second axis to be rotated and sent onto the first on, but reversed.
        Returns:
        The image with planes generated by the two axis rotated.
        See Also:
        ImageDomainTransform.getPlaneRotated90(wrapScienceJ.wrapImaJ.core.CoordinateAxis, wrapScienceJ.wrapImaJ.core.CoordinateAxis)
